  "prompt": "How often do you buy new smart phones?",
  "response": "The frequency of purchasing new smartphones can vary greatly from person to person based on individual needs, preferences, and circumstances. Some people prefer to upgrade their smartphones every year to keep up with the latest technology and features, while others might choose to replace their devices less frequently, such as every two to three years, when their current phone starts to show signs of wear or becomes obsolete in terms of performance and software updates. Ultimately, how often one buys a new smartphone depends on their budget, technological requirements, and the lifespan of their current device.",
